members.member:
/// 
Gets the text key for checkout step title.

Text resource should be provided by extension package by using 'resx' file(s).

member.remarks:
 Example of usage:
 
 // call "Success" method if you've detected the product as configurable:
 return ConfigurableProductDetectionResult.Success();

 // otherwise, call "Failure" method:
 return ConfigurableProductDetectionResult.Failure();

example.para:
Storing cardholder's CVV code during checkout so that it will be available on subsequent checkout steps.

string cvv = "123";
Api.SecureInMemoryStorage.Remember("cvv", cvv); // the storage is isolated per extension and per user account.

By default absolute expiration is enabled for this storage for 20 minutes.
Alternatively you may specify custom timeout for absolute expiration:

Api.SecureInMemoryStorage.Remember("cvv", cvv, TimeSpan.FromMinutes(3));

Alternatively you can force removal of stored data immediately after it has been retrieved by calling 
. 

string cvv = Api.SecureInMemoryStorage.RetrieveAndForget("cvv");
